article.headline: Davidson 92, NC Greensboro 73
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Brendan Winters scored 18 points in the first 15 minutes and finished with 24 as Davidson beat UNC-Greensboro 92-73 Wednesday in the Southern Conference. Davidson (14-8, 7-3) also got 16 points from Ian Johnson and 14 from Jason Morton. The Wildcats shot 56 percent from the floor for the game. UNC-Greensboro rallied from a 13-point halftime deficit on Saturday against Furman, but this time the Spartans lost any chance of a comeback when Davidson went on a 16-4 run early in the second half to lead 62-35. David McClenny led UNC-Greensboro (11-13, 4-6) with 20 points. Kyle Hines added 18 points and Ricky Hickman had 17 for the Spartans.
